Rapper Mohbad has reunited with his boss, Naira Marley and other Marlian music acts after he called them out during the recent NDLEA saga. In the late hours of February 24, 2022, Marlian music acts, Zinoleesky and Mohbad were arrested with four others for allegedly being in possession of drugs. According to the NDLEA spokesman, Femi Babafemi, some quantities of Cannabis sativa and Molly were recovered from their apartment and car.” Mohbad, who was released the same day, went on Instagram live while speaking in his local dialect(Yoruba) mixed with English, alleged members of the Marlian music team were after his life, naming his label boss Naira Marley, Zinoleesky and others.   Five top African music legends     I didn’t hit a lady and run away, Timaya reacts     My birthday wish at 33, by Yemi Alade   In a new development, the rapper was seen in the company of his Marlian music family, including Naira Marley, Zinoleeskey, and others as they shared jokes and laughed. The video was shared by Naira Marley on his Instagram page to douse any feeling of acrimony from the public towards his team. The video caption read: “As a Marlian.” Taking to the comment section, Mohbad wrote: “Family.”